&lt;h3&gt;The Role&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about advancing the data science craft and leading work that drives measurable business impact across teams?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join Mentimeter as a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Data Scientist&lt;/strong&gt;, where you will play a pivotal role in shaping how data science supports our Enterprise go-to-market motions and helps Mentimeter make better strategic decisions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Data is central to how Mentimeter succeeds. At Mentimeter, the Catalyst department is on a mission to realise our company strategy and drive innovation, growth, and impact throughout the company by using data, automations and generative AI. In this role, you will collaborate with cross functional teams, senior stakeholders, and company leaders to identify high impact opportunities and turn them into data science solutions that improve decision making, customer outcomes, and revenue growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join the Revenue Analytics team, working at the intersection of analytics, data science, revenue operations, and business. Your work will not only influence team and functional outcomes, but also contribute to broader cross functional goals across our go-to-market organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead data science initiatives and workstreams for our Enterprise go-to-market motions, from opportunity discovery and problem framing through to delivery, adoption, and impact measurement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, build, and productionise machine learning models and data products such as predictive scoring, clustering, forecasting, segmentation, recommendation, and prioritisation models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and shape high impact opportunities across retention, engagement, revenue growth, sales efficiency, customer lifecycle, and go-to-market performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Revenue Operations, Product Analytics, Analytics Engineers as well as senior business stakeholders and company leaders to align priorities and drive impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set and evolve data science craft standards, including best practices for modelling, code quality, deployment, monitoring, documentation, automation, and responsible use of AI.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and guide data scientists, analysts, and cross functional partners, helping raise the quality and impact of data science work across the function.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate recommendations and complex analyses in a way that influences decisions across different levels of the organisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We believe you have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A minimum of &lt;strong&gt;8+ years of relevant experience&lt;/strong&gt; in data science, analytics, machine learning, or a closely related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record of leading data science projects or workstreams end-to-end, including problem framing, stakeholder alignment, technical delivery, adoption, and impact measurement.&lt;/li&gt;
